description: This continuation of Mathematics 120 covers methods and applications of integration and introduces multivariable calculus. May include geometric and Taylor series. Prerequisite: Mathematics 120 or equivalent, or Mathematics Placement Recommendation. Credit may be earned for either Mathematics 126 or 128, but not both. Offered each semester.
name: Calculus II
notes: Emphasizes applications to biology and medicine.
